{
  "texts": [
    "Related works propose data synthesizers for testing machine learning tools [3], [9] and social graph generation [10].There has been rapid growth in the application of LLMs to solving numerous problems, including generating test and training data in research.",
    "Schick et al. [11] used GPT2-XL to generate synthetic datasets from scratch which, without the cost of manually labeling or fine-tuning a large model, were then used to train smaller more efficient models which exhibited strong performance in standard benchmarks compared to expensive models trained on real data.",
    "Bhavya [12] leveraged LLMs to address the challenge of low resources for information extraction by using LLMs to generate pseudo labels and generate synthetic data.",
    "Anaby-Tavor et al. [13] describes a GPT2 fine-tuned on a small existing dataset which can then be used to synthesize new labeled sentences with the augmented datasets producing improved classifier performance.",
    "In Li et al. [14], LLMs demonstrated strong reasoning abilities as automatic data annotators, generating question-answer annotations for chart images."
  ]
}